Salvation
How can I know if I am truly saved?
Understanding the assurance of salvation is a question that has been asked by countless believers throughout the history of Christianity. The question, "How can I know if I am truly saved?" touches the very heart of our faith and relationship with God. To address this profound question, we must delve into the teachings of the Bible, the witness of the Holy Spirit, and the transformative evidence of a life changed by Christ.
Biblical Assurance of Salvation
The Bible provides several assurances that can help believers know they are truly saved. One of the foundational scriptures is found in the Gospel of John. Jesus Himself assures us in John 10:27-29:
"My sheep hear my voice, and I know them, and they follow me. I give them eternal life, and they will never perish, and no one will snatch them out of my hand. My Father, who has given them to me, is greater than all, and no one is able to snatch them out of the Father's hand."
